                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rytan said that Theft of Thought and Scyers Trespass were out form of self only mana regen.  I just wanted to point out that for these two spells each take up a spell gem, while most of the other classes spells only take up a buff slot.  This tends to make them more situational than they already are.
<br />

<br />
If they stick to this line of reasoning then we need to get them to change the recast timer so that the spell can be memed and used and then swapped out.
<br />

<br />
I'm not saying that we should be able to cast it more often, but right now it is implemented as a pre-cast timer even though it is called recast.
<br />

<br />
Now that I'm thinking about it that would be a great change all over the place.  I hate losing a spell gem so that I can cast NDT or Boon.  The only other spells that I know of that have this kind of issue are DA and Speed of Cheetah.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: darkred">Iumarex Mistweaver
<br />
Coercer [Retired]
<br />
Quellious</span></span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
