                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you're charming, slow isn't as critical, since the monster is dying that much faster because of your pet.  You can get away with using Tepid Deeds, since I doubt you could even land Forlorn Deeds before the monster is dead (in a normal LDoN at least).  Heck, there are times where I don't even slow the first MoB if we have more than one in camp, because by the time I finish locking down the adds, the first one is already dead or close to.
<br />

<br />
Scryer's Trespass is nice, but if they want to make us happy, they would let us cast this on any MoB, not just caster MoBs (ditto for Mind Wrack).  There's a precedent for such a thing, i.e., Shadow Knight Zevfeer's.
<br />

<br />
Theft of Thought is still broken for 55+ MoBs as far as I know, so I don't count that spell.
<br />

<br />
If you don't have Gather Mana and Hastened Gathering 3, I highly recommend getting them or, at the very least, Gather Mana.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Prov, Wood Elf Enchanter of Qeynos (EQ2)
