                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I absolutely agree my husband runs LOM because he's doing so much compared to me.  As our group's puller, slower, CCer, he's casting mezz, paci, slows, tash, rune, NDT, etc, whereas I'm tossing around a couple heals, a vie on the MT, and the occasional nuke or cure...  
<br />

<br />
But that's my point.  I saw someone say that clerics deserve better mana regen because we do more.  I suppose that is probably true if you have to do a lot of spam heals like I read they do in GoD.  But for normal LDoNs at least, it seems like the demands on enchanter mana are <span style="font-style: italic">at least </span>equal to a cleric and yet you get less mana regen unless you're lucky enough to find a caster to suck.    <img src="images/smiles/icon_eek.gif" alt="icon_eek.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
And I DO tell my husband to stop slowing periodically to try to even out the mana drain, but it's hard to break him of the habit.  ) I also tell him to not do the rune that costs mana on himself unless he can afford it -- as long as he warns me so I can "pre-heal" with a heal over time instead.
<br />

<br />
