                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In GoD you do use a lot of spam heals or rather use an assist healing technique.  I generally solo vxed/tipt by 3 boxing(since no one wanted to help me camp BiC parts =/).  And my chanter and the cleric's mana normally stay about even, with pulling(paci/tash) and CC + charm(I have slow staff so that's not in the equation).  Our mana stays about the same, Holy Light drains a good portion of mana for the healing it provides.
<br />

<br />
Generally in Ldon or non high end (high end meaning areas where you're tanking stuff hitting for 1200+ quad with rampage or sometimes flurry.) areas a chanter's mana will be hurting more than almost any other class cause of our low overtime mana regen, however in higher end areas the other classes have to almost soley depend on their poor dmg/mana or healing/mana ratio spells as opposed to better balanced spells dmg/mana or healing/mana wise.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Lelyia
<br />
